  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Top, tail and chop the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Heat a medium-sized pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat, then once hot, add the<strong> chopped courgette</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, transfer it to a large bowl and reserve the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678183030008-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678183030008-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678183030008-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678183030008-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1678183030008-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, place the <strong>salmon fillets</strong>, skin-side down, on a clean chopping board</p><p>Hold the tail end firmly and using a sharp knife, make a cut between the flesh and skin and continue to cut along the length of the fillet away from yourself until the skin comes away from the fillet, discard the skin</p><p>Tip: Keep your knife flat against the board to stop you from cutting through the skin!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678183036336-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678183036336-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678183036336-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678183036336-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1678183036336-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>skinless salmon fillets</strong> into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped salmon</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the softened courgette with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>salmon & courgette mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678183044398-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678183044398-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678183044398-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678183044398-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678183044398-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with 20g<span class=\"text-danger\"> [40g]</span> <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add 20g <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 250ml<strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml] </span><strong>milk</strong> into the <strong>roux</strong>, a little at a time, and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your<strong> béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678183058362-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678183058362-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678183058362-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678183058362-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678183058362-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>béchamel sauce</strong> from the heat</p><p>Add the <strong>pesto</strong> and<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> to the pot with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and whisk everything together until well combined – this is your <strong>pesto béchamel</strong></p><p>Peel <strong>half </strong>the <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings (save the rest for later!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678183072290-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678183072290-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678183072290-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678183072290-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678183072290-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Layer 1/3 of the <strong>salmon & courgette mix</strong> over the bottom of an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>, then top with 2 <strong>lasagne sheets</strong>, being careful not to overlap the pasta, then top with 1/3<strong> </strong>of the <strong>pesto béchamel</strong></p><p>Repeat this process until you end up with a final layer of<strong> pesto béchamel</strong></p><p>Tip: You may need to layer differently depending on the size of your dish!</p><p>Grate<strong> </strong>the<strong> remaining Italian hard cheese </strong>on top</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678183079749-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678183079749-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678183079749-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678183079749-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678183079749-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until the pasta is cooked – this is your <strong>salmon & courgette pesto lasagne</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>rocket</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once the lasagne is nearly cooked, toss the <strong>rocket</strong> and the <strong>remaining balsamic vinegar</strong> in a large bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your <strong>rocket</strong> <strong>salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
